@page "/"

<PageTitle>Dispatcher</PageTitle>

<div class="dispatcher-page">
    <div class="dispatcher-hero">
        <div>
            <h1>Dispatcher</h1>
            <p>
                Minimal operator UI foundation for the Dispatcher SCADA platform.
            </p>
        </div>

        <div class="dispatcher-hero__badge">
            Sprint 010
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="dispatcher-grid">
        <section class="dispatcher-card">
            <h2>Backend foundation</h2>
            <p>
                Backend modules are already split into domain-oriented libraries.
            </p>
            <ul>
                <li>Objects</li>
                <li>Devices</li>
                <li>Tags</li>
                <li>Runtime</li>
                <li>Historian</li>
                <li>Events</li>
                <li>Alarms</li>
                <li>API</li>
                <li>Realtime</li>
            </ul>
        </section>

        <section class="dispatcher-card">
            <h2>Frontend foundation</h2>
            <p>
                This Blazor WebAssembly app is the starting point for the future operator workspace.
            </p>
            <ul>
                <li>Minimal shell</li>
                <li>Navigation</li>
                <li>Placeholder pages</li>
                <li>Future API client</li>
                <li>Future realtime gateway client</li>
            </ul>
        </section>

        <section class="dispatcher-card">
            <h2>MVP focus</h2>
            <p>
                The current sprint prepares a minimal operator interface and documents remaining MVP limitations.
            </p>
            <ul>
                <li>System overview</li>
                <li>Runtime placeholder</li>
                <li>Events placeholder</li>
                <li>Alarms placeholder</li>
                <li>MVP stabilization</li>
            </ul>
        </section>
    </div>
</div>